<p>You haven't saved your place in this content before. But you can start now, if you want!</p>

<p class="help">Eardogger uses a URL prefix to figure out which bookmark you want it to move. Usually you just want the domain name part, like <code>https://comic.example.com/</code>. But if there are other serials hosted on the same site, you might want to include part of the path so you can dogear them separately, like <code>https://example.com/one-particular-comic</code>.</p>

<form id="create-dogear" method="post" action="/mark">
  <label>Initial dogear location</label>
  <div class="mock-input">{{url}}</div>
  <input name="current" type="hidden" value="{{url}}" />

  <label for="prefix">URL prefix</label>
  <input name="prefix" type="text" autofocus maxlength="100" value="{{url}}" />

  <label for="display_name">Name (optional)</label>
  <input name="display_name" type="text" maxlength="200" />

  <button type="submit" id="submit-dogear">Create new dogear</button>
</form>
